<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="149" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,872,152,214]" box="[151,264,188,214]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
(
<figureCitation box="[161,253,188,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,260,1815,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-143@2.[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus lincangensis sp. nov. A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B–C. dorsal view, D. lateral view; E–G. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view, F. apical view, G. ventral view; H. habitus in in lateral view; A–H. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321615" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321615/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Figure 1</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,260,1330]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,219,260,286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Male.</emphasis>
Body medium, stout. Fastigium verticis about 1.6 times as wide as scape (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1183,260,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,260,1815,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-143@2.[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus lincangensis sp. nov. A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B–C. dorsal view, D. lateral view; E–G. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view, F. apical view, G. ventral view; H. habitus in in lateral view; A–H. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321615" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321615/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Figure 1A</figureCitation>
). Eyes longer than the length of scape; ocellus indistinct. Face with impressed dots. Anterior margin of pronotum slightly projected in the middle, posterior margin slightly concave in middle (
<figureCitation box="[752,902,332,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,260,1815,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-143@2.[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus lincangensis sp. nov. A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B–C. dorsal view, D. lateral view; E–G. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view, F. apical view, G. ventral view; H. habitus in in lateral view; A–H. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321615" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321615/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
Figure 1B 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[866,880,332,358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">–</emphasis>
C
</figureCitation>
). Fore coxae with a spinule. Ventral margins of the fore and middle tibiae with 5 pairs of spines, including one pair of smaller apical spines. Ventral margins of hind femora with 6-9 internal and 11 external spines, and the external spines obviously longer than the internal spines; dorsal margin of hind tibiae with 4-5 external and 6 internal spines; apices with 1 pair of dorsal spines and 2 pairs of ventral spines. Wings reduced to minute pads not reaching hind margin of corresponding notum (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1374,476,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,260,1815,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-143@2.[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus lincangensis sp. nov. A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B–C. dorsal view, D. lateral view; E–G. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view, F. apical view, G. ventral view; H. habitus in in lateral view; A–H. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321615" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321615/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Figure 1D</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites second and third each with two rows of very small stridulatory pegs. Ninth abdominal tergite nearly globular projected, the central split longitudinally into two lobes, the basal area enlarged, and the lateral margin of the apical area with a pair of spine-like processes, crossed and pointing ventrad and inwards, apices sharp (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,260,1815,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-143@2.[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus lincangensis sp. nov. A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B–C. dorsal view, D. lateral view; E–G. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view, F. apical view, G. ventral view; H. habitus in in lateral view; A–H. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321615" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321615/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
Figure 1E 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[182,196,620,646]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">–</emphasis>
F
</figureCitation>
). Cerci slender and subconical. Basal area of subgenital plate wider and the two-thirds of apical section gradually narrowing, posterior margin with triangular concave, the lateral lobe triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1091,1207,656,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,260,1815,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-143@2.[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus lincangensis sp. nov. A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B–C. dorsal view, D. lateral view; E–G. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view, F. apical view, G. ventral view; H. habitus in in lateral view; A–H. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321615" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321615/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Figure 1G</figureCitation>
); styli inserted laterally of one third the base of the lateral margin of subgenital plate, conical, apices obtuse (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1269,692,718]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,260,1815,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-143@2.[151,1436,450,1790]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eremus lincangensis sp. nov. A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B–C. dorsal view, D. lateral view; E–G. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view, F. apical view, G. ventral view; H. habitus in in lateral view; A–H. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321615" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321615/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Figure 1G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,260,1330]" box="[199,410,728,755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,728,754]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,260,1330]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,764,790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body yellowish brown. Face and genae black. Eyes brownish. Pronotum with light brown spots. Apices of hind femora and apices of hind tibiae black, spines of hind femora black. Spines of male ninth abdominal tergites black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,260,1330]" box="[199,1298,872,901]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,453,872,898]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Body: ³ 16.91; Pronotum: ³ 3.77; Tegmina: ³ 0.65; hind femora: ³ 8.70.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
